         <abstract id="aspace_17e4eeb893dab6c12483a20ccdedee2c">Elizabeth Hargrave is an Episcopal
            lay woman and multi-issue activist who served as the Chair of the Davidson County (N.C.)
            Commissioners, the N.C. Council of Churches Committee for Equal Rights, and Episcopal
            Diocese of N.C. Collection contains religious and activist conference and workshop
            materials, printed materials, clippings, a campaign T-shirt, one audiocassette,
            photographs, Davidson County (N. C.) Commissioner campaign materials, Charlotte Women's
            Political Caucus materials, and files related to public education in North Carolina.
            Acquired as part of the Sallie Bingham Center for Women's History and
            Culture.</abstract>
